\subsection{Ablation studies.}
To quantify the contribution of preprocessing and key hyperparameters, we conduct additional ablations on the validation set. Since the dataset is high-dimensional and the test set is noisy, we focus on (i) the impact of scaling and train-time noise augmentation, and (ii) the sensitivity of KNN to the neighborhood size $k$. Unless otherwise stated, KNN uses PCA dimension 50.
